content:
The **lock-up agreements** are agreements entered into in connection with the Business Combination by **the Sponsor, certain BowX officers, and certain WeWork officers and stockholders** under which they agree, for the applicable **lock-up period** (one year or nine months, depending on the agreement), **not to**:

- **Sell or otherwise dispose of** (or agree to sell/dispose of) any shares of **New WeWork common stock** they hold immediately after Closing (the “Lock-Up Shares”);
- Enter into any **swap or similar arrangement** that transfers, in whole or in part, the **economic consequences of ownership** of those Lock-Up Shares; or
- **Publicly announce** an intention to do any of the above during the lock-up period.
